        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Concerning Bank of St. Louis.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>My Dear <persName>Son</persName></p>

<p>I have enclosed to you a proxy for the Election of <persName>Directors </persName>to the
<placeName>Bank of [St Louis]</placeName> which you will be good a[nough to] have 
properly Executed and returned by Bill&#8212; I had a letter from <persName>Stephen F
Austin</persName> who said that in Consequence of some difficulty with the
Other <persName>Bank </persName>no Discounts will take place untill the paper arrives
from <placeName>New York</placeName> and that he wishes you to try and arrange with
<persName>Henry Elliott</persName>&#8212;our Dear little <persName>Boy </persName>is not as well as I could Wish
I hope <persName>Emily </persName>may return this Week</p>

<p>from what <persName>Stephen </persName>says your Note has not been discounted</p>

<p><persName>Moses Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p><placeName>Durham Hall</placeName> <date when="1817-01-17">Jany-17th-l817</date></p>

<p>I expect <persName>Emily </persName>has given hir Proxy to <persName>Stephn </persName>in <placeName>St Louis</placeName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Mr James Bryan</persName> <placeName>Hazel Cottage</placeName></p>

        </div1>
    </body>
